Module mesakit.graph.core
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph.specifications.library.attributes

Class AttributeReference<Referent extends com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject & com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.lifecycle.Initializable>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.specifications.library.attributes.AttributeReference<Referent>
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
public class AttributeReference<Referent extends com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject & com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.lifecycle.Initializable> extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
Manages a referent (a value that's referred to by a reference) Attributes in an AttributeStore. References are lazy-loaded with load() and can be unloaded with unload(). An attribute reference has a field name and a factory that will create a referent if one needs to be allocated.

The kind of attribute being managed can be retrieved with attribute() and the archive to load from can be attached with attach(FieldArchive). When a referent is loaded, onLoaded(NamedObject) is called and when an attribute is allocated, onAllocated() is called.

The remaining methods in attribute reference are methods for retrieving and storing different kinds of values in the referent object. Many of these methods take a Quantizable rather than a specific primitive key value. This permits any quantizable object to be used as a key. For example, all GraphElements are Indexable and index-able objects are Quantizable, so an Edge (which is a graph element) can be used as an index into an array. The quantum (long value) is just the index in this case.

jonathanl (shibo)
